originalText.text:
The manager who was working in the garage on 28 December 2021 at night was super rude.

I understand we reached the garage at 9.55 pm to pick up our car. But we still had 5 minutes to go out. Literally he shouted and was closing the gate on us so that we could not leave. We were 4 of us and two were old in 60s who wanted to use the restroom and I had to rush them out of the restroom because this manager wanted us to just leave at the very moment. Literally he closed the gate on our face and then opened once our car neared it.

Once we were out I checked my watch it was 9.59 pm. Couldn’t you have waited 1-2 minutes more?

Never coming back.

originalText.text: My wife was on the phone for 3 hours trying to find a place to park a commercial van. The operators of the parking company could not even help one of thier own and it was a nightmare. When I arrived at the location it was too small to fit inside even though we were told it would be. I had to leave my van on the ramp and we were charged an additional 60.00  for parking an oversize vehicle for 3 days. Massive amount f miscommunication and stress. I loved New York but hated the parking and lack of communication even with printed instructions spelled out for the employees.
